@node "Intro" "Introduction"
                               Introduction

 PicScaler is a graphic interface that uses the iff.library to load, scale,
 view, and save IFF ILBM Picture files.

 What it can do;
   Load picture and scale to 1/2, 1/4, 1/2 Height, 1/2 Width.
   Load "standard" size picture and scale to "standard overscan" or
   "maximum overscan".

 IFF ILBM Picture types that work;
   LORES
   INTERLACE
   SUPER BITMAP
   SUPER BITMAP LACE
   HALFBRITE
   HALFBRITE LACE
   HIRES
   HIRES LACE
   MEDRES

 IFF ILBM types that do not work;

   HAM         - scales correctly but converts it to EHB
   HAM LACE    - ditto
   animations  - nope
   brushes     - crashes for some reason so made it not load them
   24 bit      - ??? I never tried it...


 PicScaler is written in ARexx, then crunched using The ReXXmAsHeR v0.4g.
@endnode

@node "Install" "Install / Setup"
Install / Setup

 You can install PicScaler by hand or by clicking the Install button below.

 Install button only works if the Current Directory is where you unarched
 the PicScaler archive. Or you can cd to the dir you unarched to and from
 the shell enter "RX PicScaler_Install.rexx".

 By Hand:

 1. Copy the two library files included in this archive libs/ directory to
    your LIBS: assigned directory.

    libs/apig.library        (included in archive)
    libs/iff.library         (included in archive)

    1a. You must also have the following libraries in your LIBS: assigned
        directory;
 
        asl.library              (supplied with WB2+)
        mathieeedoubbas.library  (supplied with WB2+)
        rexxsyslib.library       (supplied with WB2+)
        rexxsupport.library      (supplied with WB2+)

 2. Copy the included files "PicScaler", "Run_PicScaler", and
    "Run_PicScaler.info" to .... well... wherever you want. If you do not
    plan on starting PicScaler from the Workbench, then you don't need the
    two Run_files at all - just copy PicScaler to your C: directory. But
    from Workbench you will need the two Run_files - this is because if you
    run a RexxMasher compressed file from an icon, it will give a "Software
    Error" on exit. It is a (very nasty) little bug in the RexxMasher
    program.

 You must have RexxMast already running before you start PicScaler. You can
 either drop RexxMast in your WBStartup drawer, or add it to your
 user-startup.

 PicScaler requires Amiga OS 2.0+. I have no way of testing it, but am
 pretty sure it will also work with OS 3+.

                          @{" Install PicScaler Now " rx "PicScaler_Install.rexx"}  

@endnode

