@node "ScaleTo" "Scale to:
 These gadgets decide what to scale the loaded picture to.

 The "1/2 Scale" work nicely but the "1/4 Scale" seems to lose it. But if
 you 1/2 scale a picture, save it, load the scaled picture and 1/2 scale
 it again, it does a decent job.

 It seems to do a good job converting standard resolution pictures to
 Overscan. There is no check to see if a picture is overscan or not. When
 you scale it to "Stnd Overscan" the picture will be scaled "Width * 1.1"
 and "Height * 1.2". When you scale it to "Max Overscan" the picture will
 be scaled "Width * 1.15" and "Height * 1.205".

@endnode
@node "SaveAs" "Save as:"
 Toggles between Save as "Picture" or "Brush".
@endnode
@node "Load" "Load Picture"
 Pops up an ASL file requester to choose input IFF ILBM Picture file.
@endnode
@node "ViewPic" "View Picture"
 Display loaded picture.
@endnode
@node "ScalePic" "Scale Picture"
 Scale the loaded picture to the scale selected in the "Scale to:" buttons.
@endnode
@node "ViewScaled" "View Scaled"
 View the scaled picture.

 Doesn't always display overscan scales quite right, but saves them OK.
@endnode
@node "SaveScaled" "Save Scaled"
 This gadget will pop up an ASL file requester to choose the path and
 filename to save the scaled picture or brush to. The default filename
 will be "picture_name.new_size".

 Example;
 If you load a LORES 320x200 picture called "Some.pic" and you scaled it
 to 1/2 Scale, the suggested Picture save filename would be
 "Some.pic.160x100". The suggested Brush save filename would be
 "Some.pic.160x100.bru".

 The brush saving seems to leave some garbage on the lower and right
 borders that will need to be cleaned up in a paint program. There is
 a bug in either the iff.library or apig.library - I've checked my math
 and had to write some kludges to get it to work as well as it does.
 
 Saving a Picture works fine though.
@endnode

@node "History" "PicScaler History"
 PicScaler v1.0 (29 Jun 95); First public release.

 Its free. I don't think its works well enough to ask anything for it..
 other than maybe suggestions or words of acknowledgment.
